Package line is a helper containing rule declaration helpers called O() and I().

In the future there should be other systems to declare rules.
This one is code-like, with rules containing subrules:

O("EXPR", rules(
    O("CHOICE _"),
    O("CHOICE", f....)
))

Line is an almost empty interface
that OLine and ILine implement.

Notable methods:

* OLine.ToRule(parentRule, accessBy)
* ILine.ToRules(parentRule)
* GetRule(name, rule, parentRule, attrs)

Ratpack is top-down parser. In original joeson.coffee implementation,
the pump is initialized by a top-level O() toRule call, and then (in pseudo-code):

+-----------+
|+----------+-----------------------------------------+                            
|| OLine    v                                         |                            
|| func toRule:                                       |     +--------------------------------------------------+                          
||   if not name and ...                              | .---+>func GetRule(name, rule, parentRule, attrs) {    |                          
||      ...                                           |/    |     ...                                          |                          
||   else if not name? and index? ...                 |     |     if rule instanceOf Array                     |                          
||      name = ...                                   /|     |         rule = rule.toRule parentRule name:name  |                          
||   rule =  GetRule(name, rule, parentRule, attrs) / |     |     ...             ======                       |                          
||   ...     =======--------------------------------  |     | }                      |                         |  
||                                                    |     +------------------------+-------------------------+  
|+----------------------------------------------------+                              |
|                                                                                    |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

As you notice, it's a cross-recursion, which ultimately will parse all the
grammar. The same is also true here in go, even though the GetRule has been inlined
in ILine.ToRule and OLine.ToRule

